# BUG-035: Signals Endpoint Aggregation Missing allowDiskUse

## Problem Statement

The `get_recent_articles_for_entity()` function in the signals API endpoint uses an aggregation pipeline (added in BUG-032) that includes `$sort` and `$group` stages without `allowDiskUse=True`. This pipeline has not yet hit the 32MB memory limit, but will as data volume grows — the same root cause as BUG-034.

### Root Cause

The BUG-032 fix added a `$group` + `$sort` deduplication stage to the aggregation pipeline in `signals.py`, but did not include `allowDiskUse=True`. This is a ticking time bomb — the same class of bug that crashed the signals page in BUG-034.

---

## Solution

Add `allowDiskUse=True` to all `.aggregate()` calls in the signals endpoint file.

### Changes Required

**File:** `src/crypto_news_aggregator/api/v1/endpoints/signals.py`

**`get_recent_articles_for_entity()` — BUG-032 pipeline**
```python
# Before
cursor = collection.aggregate(pipeline)

# After
cursor = collection.aggregate(pipeline, allowDiskUse=True)
```

Audit the full file for any other `.aggregate()` calls and apply the same fix.

